HEADWORD: Jockeyship
<hw>Jock"ey*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The art, character, or
position, of a jockey; the personality of a jockey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go flatter Sawney for his <qex>jockeyship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chatterton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where can at last his <qex>jockeyship</qex> retire?</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>jockey shorts</ent>⟦br⟧
